verses.text:
And the king spake unto Ashpenaz the master of his eunuchs,
that he should bring \add certain\add* of the children of Israel,
and of the king’s seed, and of the princes;

Daniel answered in the presence of the king, and said, The
secret which the king hath demanded cannot the wise \add men\add*,
the astrologers, the magicians, the soothsayers, shew unto the king;

The tree that thou sawest, which grew, and was strong, whose
height reached  unto the heaven, and the sight thereof to all the
earth;

And whereas the king saw a watcher and an holy one coming
down from heaven, and saying, Hew the tree down, and destroy it;
yet leave the stump of the roots thereof in the earth, even with a
band of iron and brass, in the tender grass of the field; and let it be
wet with the dew of heaven, and \add let\add* his portion \add be\add*
with the beasts of the field, till seven times pass over him;

Then they brought the golden vessels that were taken out of
the temple of the house of God which \add was\add* at Jerusalem;
and the king, and his princes, his wives, and his concubines, drank in them.

And a stone was brought, and laid upon the mouth of the den;
and the king sealed it with his own signet, and with the signet of his
lords; that the purpose might not be changed concerning Daniel.

And he said unto me, Unto two thousand and three hundred days;
then shall the sanctuary be cleansed.\f + \fr 8.14  \ft days: Heb. evening
morning\f*\f + \fr 8.14  \ft cleansed: Heb. justified\f*

And I Daniel fainted, and was sick \add certain\add* days;
afterward I rose up, and did the king’s business; and I was astonished
at the vision, but none understood \add it\add*.

And I prayed unto the \nd LORD\nd* my God, and made my confession,
and said, O Lord, the great and dreadful God, keeping the covenant
and mercy to them that love him, and to them that keep his commandments;

And whiles I \add was\add* speaking, and praying, and confessing
my sin and the sin of my people Israel, and presenting my supplication
before the \nd LORD\nd* my God for the holy mountain of my God;

Then said he, Knowest thou wherefore I come unto thee? and now will I
return to fight with the prince of Persia: and when I am gone forth,
lo, the prince of Grecia shall come.

And the king of the south shall be strong, and \add one\add*
of his princes; and he shall be strong above him, and have dominion;
his dominion \add shall be\add* a great dominion.

Many shall be purified, and made white, and tried; but the
wicked shall do wickedly: and none of the wicked shall understand;
but the wise shall understand.
